result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel J. Rosebrook was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Cases 13CF416 & 14CF198 recalled together at 3:18 pm [Clerk SH]
Defendant Daniel J. Rosebrook in court, in-custody, with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek. ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court reviews that case 13CF416 is only being called for reference; plea/sentencing only on 14CF198

14CF198:
Constitutional rights given; plea of "Guilty" entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 3 years, with conditions:
--to serve 5 days in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber, consecutive
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--To undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--No possession or consumption of illegal drugs
--To pay costs of $268
--To pay $250 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
--To pay Officer OT costs of $172.27

Days credit for time already served: 131 days
Felony Firearm/Voting Prohibitions Warnings Form Given
Court reminds Mr. Rosebrook that his bond/conditions of release in case 13CF416 remain in effect & of the upcoming trial dates which remain on the calendar
Court informs Mr. Rosebrook to supply Atty Svehlek with any change of address within 48 hours of change
Recess: 3:38 pm

NEXT: 13CF416 to remain as scheduled

Cases 13CF416 & 14CF198 called together at 2:30 pm [Clerk SH]
Defendant Daniel J. Rosebrook in court, in-custody, with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek. ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Teuber: At past hearing did express that there was possible resolution of trial. Have been in contact with victim & she concurred that she was accepting of any resolution proposed. Atty Svehlek has been diligently trying to get that agreement in writing, but was unable before today's hearing, presents basis. Appears that there is resolution on all matters. 
Atty Svehlek: Would request that matter be set next week for plea/sentencing otherwise use the November 4th date for plea/sentencing
ADA Teuber informs the Court that she is not available next week Thursday/Friday and Juvenile calendar on Tuesday
Court/Counsel discuss Defendant's liberties/scheduling
off-record: 2:38 - 2:39 pm for counsel to discuss
ADA Teuber informs the Court that if they proceed with 14CF198 today, the Defendant's liberties would not be affected & leave the other matter calendared for FSSC & JT and do change of plea on FSSC date.
Atty Svehlek: Agreed
Recess: 2:41 pm
Jury trial on November 10/11, 2014 at 08:30 am.
Final status/scheduling conference on November 4, 2014 at 09:00 am.
Status conference on October 16, 2014 at 02:30 pm.

Cases 13CF416 & 14CF198 called together at 9:24 am [Clerk SH]
Defendant Daniel J. Rosebrook in court, in-custody, with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Svehlek: Have had conversations with the State and are on the path to possibly resolve both matters. Requests the matters come off the trial calendar and have both matters set for STC in approximately 30 days.
ADA Teuber: After motion and new evidence, there does appear to be resolution in matter. Did ask Atty Svehlek for time to speak with victim regarding resolution, but have not been able to speak with victim. Join in the adjournment request. If matter does proceed to trial, the next date should be final date. Victim Rights Compliance verified - victim did not request speedy trial in this case. But do believe time to speak with victim is needed.
Counsel agree that if 13CF416 goes to trial, will need 2 days
Court presents basis and grants request to adjourn

NEXT: BOTH CASES: (1)  Schedule STC 10/16/14 at 2:30 pm (30 minutes) - Send notices (2) Schedule FSSC 11/4/14 at 9:00 am - Send notices (3) Schedule JT 11/10-11/14 at 8:30 - Send notices
NOH for defendant sent to LKA//hearing dates are PTC on 7-2-14 & STC on 9-9-14//notices also sent to the defendant at the jail
Status conference on September 9, 2014 at 09:00 am.

Cases 13CF416 & 14CF198 called together at 8:45 am [Clerk SH]
Defendant Daniel J. Rosebrook in court, in custody, with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek. DA Susan V. Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Svehlek: Have not reached resolution to cases, underlying case is set for FSSC & JT. Requests that the 14CF198 case track with 13CF416 and also be set for FSSC & JT at the same date and time
DA Happ requests the 14CF198 case be set for STC, rather than FSSC & JT along with 13CF416, presents basis including child witnesses needing to be subpoenaed for that matter
Court presents basis and informs parties that It will not set 14CF198 for trial, but for STC
Recess: 8:49 am 

NEXT: (1) 13CF416 to remain as scheduled (2) 14CF198: Schedule STC 9/9/14 at 9:00 am - Send notices
Status conference on July 17, 2014 at 08:45 am.
Pre-trial conference on July 2, 2014 at 09:00 am.

Case called at 10:24 am [Clerk SH]
Defendant Daniel J. Rosebrook in court, in-custody, with Attorney Elizabeth F Svehlek. ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court for the record indicates that by agreement of parties are calling case a bit early, no victim rights issues

Court examines the Defendant as to rights, understanding & intent.  
Mr. Rosebrook waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Arraignment.
State files information

Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived
--maximum penalties recited
--pleas of "not guilty" entered
Upon questioning of the Court, Atty Svehlek indicates that Mr. Rosebrook's other pending matter is scheduled for trial in September & that it would be helpful to have that matter also set for STC with this case as there are no other hearings scheduled in that case except trial.
Court reminds Defendant that bond/conditions of bond remain in effect while case is pending
Recess: 10:29 am 

NEXT: (1) DA PTC scheduled for 7/2/14 at 9:00 am - Send notices (2) STC scheduled for 7/17/14 at 8:45 am - Send notices **Also schedule case 13CF416 for DA PTC and STC**
Preliminary hearing on June 17, 2014 at 10:30 am.

Case called at 2:12 pm
Defendant Daniel J. Rosebrook in cusotdy, via video from the Jefferson County jail with Attorney Elizabeth Svehlek from the Jefferson County Public Defenders Office. Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint  appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court verifies with the Defendant that the DOB lsited on the criminal complaint is correct.
Attorney Svehlek informs the Court that the Doris St. address listed on the complaint is not current and the defendant will update the parties as to a current address.
Service of Complaint admitted; reading waived; charges and maximum penalties recited
Court finds that the criminal complaint states probable cause to support Count #1
The Court finds the video connection to be sight and sound sufficient. 
Bail/Bond recommendations presented by counsel.

Court requires $2,500.00 CASH bond, with conditions: 
-No contact with Carissa Prievusch, KSZ (DOB: 2/9/04), TLZ (DOB: 11/3/01), DEZ (DOB: 7/28/00), DGB (DOB: 4/1/09) or AB
-No contact with Bobbie Bowman or Brenda Wood 
-No presence at the residence of Bobbie Bowman or Brenda Wood 
-No presence within 1000 feet of the Watertown Aquatic Center

Court will schedule Preliminary Hearing within 10 day time limit.
Mr. Rosebrook qualifies for SPD representation.

Recess:  2:23 pm
NEXT: (Notices to be mailed)
Preliminary Hearing: 6/17/14 at 10:30 am
